May be an image of food and text that says 'MTB HAT GUY'S monthly spotlight AARON'S BAITS THUMPER A deadly inshore bait designed for the salty angler looking for a natural swimming soft plastic bait that can be rigged and retrieved using different techniques. The Thumper measures 3.5" and features distinct side-to-side swimming action as it's jigged, straight retrieved, or even burned up top near the surface. Rig the Thumper on classic jig head, or keep fish on their toes by adding it to Carolina or umbrella rig. Expect to catch any inshore species feeding on minnows with this smooth swimming and easy operating soft plastic swimbait.'.

node.text: The @googansquad Revolver went into a few boxes recently. Here's a breakdown on the bait and some techniques for fishing it! What other baits from the box do you want to see some breakdowns on?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Mystery Tackle Box on August 12, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'SQUAD GOOGAN REVOLVER FLAT TAIL PREVENTS ROLL OVER TRONG #2SIZE TREBLE HOOKS WEIGHT DISTRIBUTION: DISTR Lands Lands eeryc every ROTATING FIN: Distinct plopping noise Center lacement draws strikes the hook body ojitter on retrieve Icollabwith CATCH'.

Photo by Mystery Tackle Box on August 12, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Shootin' Straight with the Googan Squad REVOLVER GEAR RECOMMENDATIONS: Rod: Medium-Heavy Heavy Casting Rod Reel: Moderate Speed Casting Reel Line: 5-20lb Monofilament or 40- 40-65lb Braid M M Cast your bait parallel to the shoreline and slowly wind around sunrise sunset, when fish are likely to be pushed up shallow and in a feeding mode.'.

Photo by Mystery Tackle Box on August 12, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Shootin' Straight with the Googan Squad REVOLVER GEAR RECOMMENDATIONS: Rod: Medium-Heavy Casting Rod Reel: Moderate Speed Casting Reel Line: 15-20lb Monofilament or 40-65lb Braid M On bright sunny days, throw the Revolver near the shadow lines created from trees, docks, bridges, or anything else that can cast shadow. Bass feel comfortable in the shade and use shade lines as ambush points to feed on smaller fish.'.
